            p.mb-3 Here's what's really concerning me. Traditional learning and AI both start the same way‚Äîwith that premature confidence spike on the Crest of Hubris. But here's where things diverge:

            .alert.alert-warning
              .d-flex.align-items-start
                i.bi.bi-exclamation-triangle.me-2.mt-1
                div
                  strong AI flattens that peak
                  |  into an extended
                  strong Mesa of Illusory Mastery
                  | . Instead of quickly hitting reality and learning from it, you stay up high way longer than you should, even though you're not gaining real understanding.

            p.mb-3 Think about it: you ask ChatGPT about climate change, it gives you this comprehensive-sounding response, and you walk away feeling informed. But climate science is incredibly complex, and that AI response was basically just a really good summary of the basics. The problem is, the AI doesn't tell you that, and you don't know to ask.

